ZH: 这家公司的管理人员都是一群官僚。
EN: The management personnel of this company are all bureaucrats.

ZH: 官僚主义会严重影响组织的效率。
EN: Bureaucracy can seriously affect the efficiency of an organization.

ZH: 他被官僚体制限制得走投无路。
EN: He is trapped by the bureaucratic system and has nowhere to turn.

ZH: 这种官僚作风已经持续了太久。
EN: This bureaucratic style has been going on for too long.

ZH: 官僚的程序常常让人感到繁琐。
EN: Bureaucratic procedures often feel cumbersome.

ZH: 这个项目因为官僚作风而拖延了很久。
EN: This project has been delayed for a long time due to bureaucratic red tape.

ZH: 他对官僚体系感到十分失望。
EN: He is very disappointed with the bureaucratic system.

ZH: 在官僚机构中，速度总是缓慢的。
EN: In bureaucratic organizations, things always move slowly.

ZH: 官僚主义使得行政效率低下。
EN: Bureaucracy leads to low administrative efficiency.

ZH: 我们需要摆脱官僚思维的束缚。
EN: We need to break free from the shackles of bureaucratic thinking.

ZH: 官僚机构需要更强调效率和创新。
EN: Bureaucratic organizations need to focus more on efficiency and innovation.

ZH: 官僚主义通常会导致决策拖延。
EN: Bureaucracy often leads to delayed decision-making.

ZH: 他的成功是因为他不受官僚体制的牵制。
EN: His success is because he is not bound by the bureaucratic system.

ZH: 这个国家的官僚体系需要进行改革。
EN: The bureaucratic system of this country needs to be reformed.

ZH: 官僚作风让很多人感到沮丧。
EN: Bureaucratic style makes many people feel frustrated.

ZH: 他对官僚主义提出了批评。
EN: He criticized bureaucracy.

ZH: 官僚的决策往往是通过繁琐的程序来实现。
EN: Bureaucratic decisions are often implemented through cumbersome procedures.

ZH: 官僚体制会抑制创新和发展。
EN: Bureaucratic systems can stifle innovation and development.

ZH: 他一直在为打破官僚体系而努力。
EN: He has been working hard to break the bureaucratic system.

ZH: 官僚作风是这个国家经济发展的障碍。
EN: Bureaucratic style is hindering the economic development of this country.
